Oh joy, another chance to dive into the world of JavaScript DOM manipulation! Here's a quick and dirty way to select all checkboxes on a page with a single click:

```javascript
// Select all checkboxes on the page
const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');

// Function to check or uncheck all checkboxes
function toggleAllCheckboxes() {
    checkboxes.forEach(checkbox => {
        checkbox.checked = !checkbox.checked; // Inverts the checked state
    });
}

// Attach this function to a button click event for "Save"
document.querySelector('button[type="submit"]').addEventListener('click', toggleAllCheckboxes);
```

Now, when you click the "Save" button, all checkboxes will toggle their states. Just remember, this is a simple example and might not work perfectly in every scenario, especially if your checkboxes have custom behaviors or if there are other elements that interfere.

